request.description:
Read-only view of `alchemy_webhook_registry`. Use this from the dashboard to decide which chains are already wired (skip bootstrap) versus which still need it. The signing key is **never** returned — it stays encrypted at rest. To verify or rotate a key, use `POST /admin/alchemy-webhooks/signing-keys`.

Response:
```json
{
  "webhooks": [
    { "chainId": 1, "chain": "ethereum", "webhookId": "wh_...", "webhookUrl": "https://...", "createdAt": "...", "updatedAt": "..." }
  ],
  "limit": 100,
  "offset": 0,
  "hasMore": false
}
```

Returns:

```json
{
  "invoice": { ... },
  "amounts": {
    "requiredUsd": "100.00",
    "confirmedUsd": "60.00",
    "confirmingUsd": "25.00",
    "remainingUsd": "40.00",
    "overpaidUsd": "0.00"
  },
  "transactions": [
    { "chain": "ethereum", "chainId": 1, "token": "USDC", "amount": "60", "amountUsd": "60.00", "status": "confirmed", "txHash": "0x...", "fromAddress": "0x...", "toAddress": "0x...", "detectedAt": "...", "confirmedAt": "..." },
    { "chain": "polygon", "chainId": 137, "token": "USDC", "amount": "25", "amountUsd": "25.00", "status": "detected", ... }
  ]
}
```

- `amounts.*` is null for legacy single-token invoices (use `requiredAmountRaw` / `receivedAmountRaw` on the invoice itself there).
- `transactions` includes ALL statuses: `detected` / `confirmed` / `reverted` / `orphaned` — handy for debugging when received/paid look stuck.
